&lt;p&gt;Hi Anja,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reaching out! Based on your description, it looks like your website is experiencing &lt;strong&gt;mixed content issues&lt;/strong&gt;. This happens when some elements (like scripts, images, or stylesheets) are being loaded over &lt;strong&gt;HTTP&lt;/strong&gt; while the rest of your site is on &lt;strong&gt;HTTPS&lt;/strong&gt;. Many modern browsers block insecure content by default, which can cause pages or certain elements (like the navigation) to not load properly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since clearing the browser cache temporarily resolves the issue, it confirms that some resources are not consistently loading due to security restrictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;How to Fix It&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Force HTTPS for All Content&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Make sure your WordPress site URL (under &lt;strong&gt;Settings &amp;gt; General&lt;/strong&gt;) is set to &lt;strong&gt;https://&lt;/strong&gt; and not &lt;strong&gt;http://&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If your site runs on HTTPS, but some files still load over HTTP, you can use a plugin like &lt;strong&gt;Really Simple SSL&lt;/strong&gt; to automatically correct this.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check for Mixed Content Errors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You can inspect your site using the &lt;strong&gt;browser console&lt;/strong&gt; (Press F12 or right-click &amp;gt; Inspect &amp;gt; Console) to find any HTTP resources being blocked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, tools like &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.whynopadlock.com/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Why No Padlock?&lt;/a&gt; can help detect mixed content issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manually Fix Mixed Content Links&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
