&lt;p&gt;Hi there,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! I forgot to include the style.css file in the child theme. I just updated the theme with the fix. (&lt;em&gt;I attached the child theme for more convenience&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is normal‚Äîthe theme comes with only a child theme template. A child theme is meant to inherit all functionalities and styles from the parent theme while allowing you to add custom modifications safely. The functions.php file in the child theme lets you override or add custom functions without modifying the parent theme. If you need to customize templates, you can copy the necessary files from the parent theme into the child theme and modify them as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That being said, using a child theme is a bit advanced. There are already many customization options available in the theme itself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I hope it will help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Best regards&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can I¬†ask you one more thing ?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;How do you use the child theme ?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Like this is installed by default when installing poize theme¬†?¬†&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;EDITED 2 Watch the¬†error below about the child theme&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://ticksy_attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/9425630952.png&quot; alt=&quot;9425630952.png&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;¬†&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;EDITED 1 READ THE DOC&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How to set up your own Child Theme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although child themes can be a great way to add custom changes to your theme, they are most often used to customize core code taken from the parent theme. Because of this,¬†please be aware that customizations of this nature fall outside our scope of support, and we will be unable to assist you with any issues that may arise. To use the child theme, find the ‚Äúthemename-child‚Äù folder in your theme package and upload it to your¬†wp-content/themes¬†folder through FTP. As it is mainly made to be edited, we didn‚Äôt include it as a zip file, so you will have to install it manually. Once installed and activated, it will automatically inherit all parent theme features, functions, and styles.&lt;/p&gt;

